1
00:00:00,960 --> 00:00:04,635
SHINSHINMARU 88

2
00:00:04,718 --> 00:00:08,141
[Hansuke] Tanba-san agreed to
the offer to move out.

3
00:00:08,225 --> 00:00:09,561
Oh, Tanba-san.

4
00:00:09,645 --> 00:00:11,189
-[Tanba-san] Hi.
-[chuckles]

5
00:00:11,857 --> 00:00:13,569
Write something on it.

6
00:00:13,653 --> 00:00:16,407
[news reporter 1] It's that time
of year again.

7
00:00:16,491 --> 00:00:19,665
The day marking 13 years since The What.

8
00:00:19,998 --> 00:00:21,417
At this temporary housing,

9
00:00:21,502 --> 00:00:24,131
steps are being taken
to finally move everyone out.

10
00:00:24,215 --> 00:00:26,177
Talks with residents are making progress.

11
00:00:26,261 --> 00:00:27,597
SPECIAL REPORT
13 YEARS LATER, EVICTION TALKS BEGIN

12
00:00:27,681 --> 00:00:30,687
Some of the residents
are set to move out today.

13
00:00:30,770 --> 00:00:34,068
-See you later. Bye.
-[Yoshie] Call us if you need anything.

14
00:00:34,151 --> 00:00:36,364
Tora, get down, you dumb cat.

15
00:00:36,447 --> 00:00:38,410
[breathing rapidly]

16
00:00:40,455 --> 00:00:41,709
[meows]

17
00:00:42,919 --> 00:00:44,213
-See you later.
-[Hansuke] Bye.

18
00:00:44,297 --> 00:00:46,885
-Take care of yourself, Tanba-san.
-[Yoshie] See you around.

19
00:00:48,221 --> 00:00:51,729
-Eat properly, Tanba-san.
-Goodbye, Tanba-san.

20
00:00:51,854 --> 00:00:53,566
-See you.
-Bye.

21
00:00:57,991 --> 00:01:00,370
Thirteen years, huh?

22
00:01:03,126 --> 00:01:05,673
I've been here for exactly a year.

23
00:01:06,174 --> 00:01:10,098
PLAYING SHOGI WITHOUT PAWNS
IS PLAYING A LOSING GAME OF SHOGI

24
00:01:10,182 --> 00:01:12,645
[news reporter 2] Even now,
disaster victims are forced to live

25
00:01:12,729 --> 00:01:14,190
destitute lives in temporary housing.

26
00:01:14,273 --> 00:01:15,317
AT ITS PEAK, 30 FAMILIES LIVED HERE

27
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,363
Thirteen years after The What,

28
00:01:18,198 --> 00:01:20,578
what are the residents thinking now?

29
00:01:21,162 --> 00:01:23,458
[Hansuke] Tatsuya works with
an intermediary

30
00:01:23,584 --> 00:01:26,130
going to each home making offers.

31
00:01:26,214 --> 00:01:29,428
Neither the national nor local governments
can force you out.

32
00:01:30,138 --> 00:01:32,852
But Tanba-san left.

33
00:01:32,936 --> 00:01:34,313
What's Masuo saying?

34
00:01:34,397 --> 00:01:36,902
[Igawa] Everyone receives
50,000 yen for vacating.

35
00:01:36,985 --> 00:01:39,741
That's nothin'! It's only a month's rent
at the Recovery Public Housing.

36
00:01:39,825 --> 00:01:41,285
And two masks.

37
00:01:41,369 --> 00:01:42,789
[Mitsuyo] You can keep 'em!

38
00:01:43,791 --> 00:01:48,592
We'll leave, if we can live
across from Hatsu in the new place.

39
00:01:49,803 --> 00:01:51,347
It's not that nice?

40
00:01:51,431 --> 00:01:54,646
I had a look inside,
but the shower pressure was weak.

41
00:01:55,313 --> 00:01:58,027
-And the tatami mats were gaudy.
-And they want 50,000 yen for rent?

42
00:01:58,111 --> 00:01:59,155
Good morning.

43
00:01:59,698 --> 00:02:01,200
Hello.

44
00:02:01,409 --> 00:02:02,954
You making progress?

45
00:02:03,037 --> 00:02:05,835
Next, we've got a meeting
with the construction company.

46
00:02:05,918 --> 00:02:08,047
There are a ton of issues.

47
00:02:08,131 --> 00:02:09,509
We'll go to Building Four.

48
00:02:09,593 --> 00:02:11,137
You sure better.

49
00:02:13,433 --> 00:02:15,646
And I thought he was a nice guy.

50
00:02:16,063 --> 00:02:18,193
Looks like it might rain today.

51
00:02:18,276 --> 00:02:19,905
Too bad he's behind all of it.

52
00:02:19,988 --> 00:02:21,742
Yeah.

53
00:02:23,203 --> 00:02:25,750
A TOWN WITHOUT SEASONS

54
00:02:25,833 --> 00:02:28,254
[Hansuke] The first one
who displayed opposition

55
00:02:28,338 --> 00:02:30,091
was someone unexpected.

56
00:02:30,175 --> 00:02:31,344
I can't do this.

57
00:02:31,427 --> 00:02:34,726
I already barely make enough
to support a family of eight.

58
00:02:34,809 --> 00:02:36,103
How could I pay rent?

59
00:02:36,187 --> 00:02:41,698
Children are calculated at two-for-one,
so yours is a family of five.

60
00:02:41,782 --> 00:02:42,825
Huh?

61
00:02:44,328 --> 00:02:47,167
If you economize,
it's not an unreasonable amount to pay.

62
00:02:47,251 --> 00:02:48,419
We'll assist you.

63
00:02:48,504 --> 00:02:52,637
How dare you drop in all of a sudden
and tell us to leave this month.

64
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:55,433
Are you devils?
You may as well tell us to die.

65
00:02:55,518 --> 00:02:59,149
[Igawa] The government provided
this interim housing as temporary relief

66
00:02:59,233 --> 00:03:00,778
until families got on their feet.

67
00:03:00,861 --> 00:03:03,576
Can't you see? We're not on our feet yet.

68
00:03:03,659 --> 00:03:06,372
-Then quit having babies.
-Cut that out, Hamaguchi.

69
00:03:06,455 --> 00:03:08,209
Sorry.

70
00:03:08,418 --> 00:03:11,382
In this time of shrinking population,
I admire you.

71
00:03:11,465 --> 00:03:12,719
But from our view--

72
00:03:12,802 --> 00:03:15,015
-You understand how it is, right?
-Huh?

73
00:03:15,098 --> 00:03:17,102
You support your mom and two siblings.

74
00:03:17,185 --> 00:03:18,897
[Ryotaro] It's not easy, is it?

75
00:03:19,524 --> 00:03:23,156
Actually… they all left.

76
00:03:23,239 --> 00:03:24,534
You're kidding?

77
00:03:24,618 --> 00:03:26,162
Got out early, huh?

78
00:03:26,538 --> 00:03:28,709
You and your Young Men's Club,

79
00:03:28,792 --> 00:03:31,548
you said you'll make us a cafe and stuff.

80
00:03:31,632 --> 00:03:34,763
But now you're on their side,
pressuring us to get out.

81
00:03:34,846 --> 00:03:35,973
You traitor!

82
00:03:36,057 --> 00:03:38,854
Aren't you getting
child-support payments, ma'am?

83
00:03:38,937 --> 00:03:40,106
Mikki.

84
00:03:41,442 --> 00:03:44,574
[Mikki] I had you people investigated.

85
00:03:44,658 --> 00:03:46,578
Tsutomu, Shiro. Go play outside.

86
00:03:46,912 --> 00:03:48,498
[Mikki] They're not your kids, right?

87
00:03:48,582 --> 00:03:50,335
Hey, cut that out.

88
00:03:50,586 --> 00:03:54,301
Their real fathers are
all residents here, right?

89
00:03:54,844 --> 00:03:57,600
-You're really something, ma'am.
-[Tatsuya] Cut it out!

90
00:03:57,684 --> 00:04:01,817
If each of their fathers paid
10,000 yen a month,

91
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:03,946
you could pay that rent.

92
00:04:04,446 --> 00:04:05,658
Right, Sprouts?

93
00:04:05,741 --> 00:04:08,496
Are you deaf? Go play outside! Now!

94
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:10,125
They don't have to go.

95
00:04:13,423 --> 00:04:15,343
I'm sure you kids know

96
00:04:16,011 --> 00:04:19,476
who your real father is and who's a liar.

97
00:04:20,228 --> 00:04:21,230
Isn't that right?

98
00:04:22,357 --> 00:04:24,445
Ryoko, tell them your father's name.

99
00:04:26,365 --> 00:04:28,494
Ryotaro Sawagami.

100
00:04:28,579 --> 00:04:32,169
What? Are you kidding?
She's clearly half Japanese.

101
00:04:32,252 --> 00:04:33,839
That Indian laborer's her dad.

102
00:04:33,922 --> 00:04:35,760
Nobody asked you!

103
00:04:35,843 --> 00:04:37,429
-[Tatsuya] Whoa, stop!
-Nobody asked you!

104
00:04:37,513 --> 00:04:39,099
-Get out!
-[Hamaguchi] Stop it!

105
00:04:39,183 --> 00:04:40,226
[Ryotaro] Get out right now!

106
00:04:40,310 --> 00:04:42,523
[Mikki] I only addressed
the elephant in the room.

107
00:04:42,607 --> 00:04:46,531
[Hansuke] That night, Misao Sawagami,
aka Sprouts,

108
00:04:47,324 --> 00:04:50,831
left the town with just her baby.

109
00:04:57,804 --> 00:04:58,889
[in Hindi]
Farewell.

110
00:04:58,972 --> 00:05:03,147
[Hansuke in Japanese] The Immigration
Bureau arrested Ryoko's father

111
00:05:03,231 --> 00:05:06,195
for the crime of illegal employment.

112
00:05:06,278 --> 00:05:07,990
Farewell.

113
00:05:09,911 --> 00:05:11,455
[in Hindi]
Farewell.

114
00:05:15,088 --> 00:05:17,175
[in Japanese]
It's not your fault, Hansuke.

115
00:05:17,259 --> 00:05:19,179
No, it definitely is.

116
00:05:19,514 --> 00:05:21,560
[Tatsuya] Sooner or later,
it would've come out.

117
00:05:21,643 --> 00:05:23,939
Just nobody ever told anyone.

118
00:05:25,191 --> 00:05:28,364
You're wrong.
Staying silent is a great thing.

119
00:05:28,907 --> 00:05:30,661
Ignoring it is kindness.

120
00:05:30,744 --> 00:05:33,750
How can you stay silent?
People like Roku-chan and Kuma

121
00:05:33,834 --> 00:05:37,132
and Sprouts aren't normal.
We want to talk about them.

122
00:05:37,215 --> 00:05:39,386
And you'll get paid if you report it.

123
00:05:41,808 --> 00:05:43,436
I was being arrogant.

124
00:05:44,021 --> 00:05:46,025
Since I'm a good and proper person,

125
00:05:46,108 --> 00:05:48,739
I can do whatever I want
to people who aren't.

126
00:05:49,323 --> 00:05:50,784
I felt that way inside.

127
00:05:52,037 --> 00:05:53,707
So I want to apologize to everyone.

128
00:05:55,753 --> 00:05:57,047
Everyone? Who?

129
00:06:00,470 --> 00:06:02,432
Everyone's gotta leave because of you!

130
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:05,146
Tanba-san,

131
00:06:05,229 --> 00:06:07,359
and Hatsu and Masuo

132
00:06:07,442 --> 00:06:08,987
and Roku-chan

133
00:06:09,321 --> 00:06:10,824
and Katsuko.

134
00:06:15,124 --> 00:06:17,922
Huh? Is that right, Katsuko?

135
00:06:19,007 --> 00:06:26,021
That CEO's wife, her mom,
said she'll take her in for a while.

136
00:06:27,775 --> 00:06:28,860
I'm sorry.

137
00:06:29,444 --> 00:06:31,866
What are you apologizing for?

138
00:06:32,743 --> 00:06:34,246
It is a shock though.

139
00:06:34,706 --> 00:06:37,460
It's only a matter of time
before the complainers leave.

140
00:06:37,545 --> 00:06:40,718
The ones who don't pay taxes,
the ones on welfare illegally.

141
00:06:40,801 --> 00:06:42,847
Look and you'll find dirt on all of them.

142
00:06:42,930 --> 00:06:45,686
That's why nobody talked.
Not because they're kind!

143
00:06:45,769 --> 00:06:48,441
Why are they being kicked out?
What'll be built here?

144
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:50,863
[Shima] Memorial Stadium.

145
00:06:51,990 --> 00:06:53,869
It'll open this summer.

146
00:06:53,952 --> 00:06:56,081
We'll hold a festival
to celebrate the reconstruction.

147
00:06:56,165 --> 00:06:57,208
NANI ROCK FES. 2024

148
00:06:57,292 --> 00:06:58,920
[Okabe] That's really scuzzy.

149
00:06:59,004 --> 00:07:01,175
The headliner will be Maximum the Hormone.

150
00:07:01,258 --> 00:07:02,595
Wait. Hold on here.

151
00:07:03,429 --> 00:07:05,768
This place is too small for a stadium.

152
00:07:05,851 --> 00:07:11,236
[Shima] That's why it's being built on
the waterfront where access is better.

153
00:07:11,988 --> 00:07:14,660
The performers' dressing rooms,
a parking lot,

154
00:07:14,744 --> 00:07:17,165
and porta potties will be located here.

155
00:07:17,248 --> 00:07:20,004
You don't need this space for that.
It could go anywhere!

156
00:07:21,298 --> 00:07:26,183
Porta potties
and dressing rooms for a festival?

157
00:07:26,266 --> 00:07:28,730
You're kicking everyone out for that?

158
00:07:28,814 --> 00:07:33,322
Tanaka, I'll admit
that this is a nice place,

159
00:07:33,405 --> 00:07:34,951
but it's not a utopia.

160
00:07:37,455 --> 00:07:38,667
It's temporary housing.

161
00:07:39,710 --> 00:07:42,925
Normal people move out of here.

162
00:07:55,074 --> 00:07:56,118
Sorry.

163
00:07:56,619 --> 00:07:58,790
I need you to sign
this agreement by tomorrow.

164
00:08:13,194 --> 00:08:15,239
[Hansuke] I've got a lot of stuff now.

165
00:08:15,323 --> 00:08:17,870
[Tora] They're all presents though.

166
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:21,628
What should I do?

167
00:08:23,088 --> 00:08:25,928
Where the heck am I supposed to go?

168
00:08:26,011 --> 00:08:27,973
[Tora] It'll work out somehow.

169
00:08:28,934 --> 00:08:30,144
Are you coming with me?

170
00:08:30,228 --> 00:08:32,190
[Tora] What? You'd leave me behind?

171
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,987
Oh, there's a QR code.

172
00:08:44,799 --> 00:08:47,011
AGREEMENT TO VACATE TEMPORARY HOUSING

173
00:08:47,095 --> 00:08:48,472
NO SEASON SENT YOU 50,000 YEN

174
00:08:48,557 --> 00:08:49,558
[shouts in anger]

175
00:08:49,642 --> 00:08:52,690
[Hansuke] The payment for vacating
was paid in digital cash.

176
00:08:54,192 --> 00:08:58,660
The elderly who didn't have cell phones
received 50,000 yen in gift certificates.

177
00:08:58,743 --> 00:09:00,706
And here are two masks.

178
00:09:00,789 --> 00:09:03,210
Thank you for residing here for 13 years.

179
00:09:05,423 --> 00:09:06,634
Thank you.

180
00:09:07,010 --> 00:09:10,767
For you, Roku-chan,
you get 50,000 yen on a train pass card.

181
00:09:10,851 --> 00:09:13,147
Ride all you want.

182
00:09:14,149 --> 00:09:15,986
How dare she make fun of me.

183
00:09:16,069 --> 00:09:17,488
I'm not into trains!

184
00:09:17,573 --> 00:09:19,744
Power shovels are the best!

185
00:09:20,704 --> 00:09:23,417
[Kuniko] Roku-chan, carry this for me.

186
00:09:24,127 --> 00:09:26,256
There. Okay, let's go.

187
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:29,262
Over there. There.

188
00:09:29,346 --> 00:09:32,393
[noisy chatter]

189
00:09:33,479 --> 00:09:35,316
[Hansuke] On the last day,

190
00:09:35,399 --> 00:09:38,657
No Season held a farewell party.

191
00:09:38,740 --> 00:09:41,286
THANK YOU FOR RESIDING HERE FOR 13 YEARS!
FOR OUR SUSTAINABLE FUTURE!!

192
00:09:41,370 --> 00:09:43,415
[overlapping chatter]

193
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:45,504
Would you like a drink?

194
00:09:45,587 --> 00:09:49,720
Hey! Cut that out, darn it!
Quit throwing things!

195
00:09:49,804 --> 00:09:52,225
That No Season…

196
00:09:53,645 --> 00:09:55,147
Thank you.

197
00:09:56,651 --> 00:10:02,203
[noisy chatter continues]

198
00:10:06,629 --> 00:10:08,424
Hey! Get outta here!

199
00:10:08,508 --> 00:10:11,138
-Shoo! Shoo!
-Yeah, yeah.

200
00:10:11,221 --> 00:10:14,394
Any place is fine. Any place.

201
00:10:14,477 --> 00:10:17,568
Hasegawa. Bartender.
You guys write something too.

202
00:10:17,651 --> 00:10:20,156
-[Hasegawa] Are you sure it's okay?
-Of course.

203
00:10:20,239 --> 00:10:21,450
Thank you.

204
00:10:22,661 --> 00:10:24,456
Don't make any mistakes.

205
00:10:32,263 --> 00:10:33,516
-Let's go.
-Okay.

206
00:10:44,287 --> 00:10:49,840
[shouting, laughing]

207
00:10:50,090 --> 00:10:51,384
[Hansuke] Tora!

208
00:10:54,725 --> 00:10:57,396
We should have invited Tanba-san.

209
00:10:58,232 --> 00:10:59,777
Wanna call him?

210
00:10:59,944 --> 00:11:01,614
Didn't you know, Hansuke?

211
00:11:01,697 --> 00:11:03,618
Tanba-san went to live in a nursing home.

212
00:11:03,701 --> 00:11:06,206
What? Not the public housing?

213
00:11:06,289 --> 00:11:08,418
[Tatsuya] They said he's got dementia.

214
00:11:09,003 --> 00:11:10,966
And that he can't live alone anymore.

215
00:11:11,424 --> 00:11:14,765
Are you kidding? He was living alone.

216
00:11:15,266 --> 00:11:16,561
He was just fine.

217
00:11:16,644 --> 00:11:18,690
Tatsuya, is Shima-san inside?

218
00:11:18,773 --> 00:11:22,196
[Tatsuya] Whoa! Yes, he is,
but he's in a video meeting.

219
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,282
Huh?

220
00:11:23,365 --> 00:11:25,870
He sends his greetings.

221
00:11:25,954 --> 00:11:28,166
-Not like I care.
-I gotta go to the restroom.

222
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:31,214
But what's more important
than giving us a proper farewell?

223
00:11:31,298 --> 00:11:33,928
Now, now, Masuo. Let's keep on drinkin'.

224
00:11:34,012 --> 00:11:37,393
[Masuo] Just like you people want,
we'll be leavin' tomorrow.

225
00:11:37,476 --> 00:11:39,230
Scum of the earth!

226
00:11:53,635 --> 00:11:56,473
THE VERTICAL THREAD IS KATSUKO
THE HORIZONTAL THREAD IS OKABE

227
00:11:57,099 --> 00:11:59,772
Katsuko, can you come here?

228
00:11:59,855 --> 00:12:02,736
There's a 'coon dog.

229
00:12:03,278 --> 00:12:04,823
[Katsuko] "Coon dog"?

230
00:12:06,577 --> 00:12:08,831
[Kuma] Get outta here, you caterpillar.

231
00:12:09,082 --> 00:12:11,002
Nobody wants you here.

232
00:12:11,086 --> 00:12:12,965
[Hansuke] Kuma, calm down
and enjoy your drink.

233
00:12:13,048 --> 00:12:15,845
[Kuma] I'm leavin'
after I finish this one anyway.

234
00:12:17,306 --> 00:12:19,895
What the heck are you filming,
you media scum?

235
00:12:19,978 --> 00:12:21,524
Quit filmin'!

236
00:12:21,857 --> 00:12:24,404
I'm an ex-con, ya know, dammit!

237
00:12:24,487 --> 00:12:26,366
[Ryotaro] How pathetic.

238
00:12:27,953 --> 00:12:30,374
You killed someone and buried 'em, huh?

239
00:12:30,457 --> 00:12:32,587
What a stupid lie that is.

240
00:12:33,338 --> 00:12:37,138
I bet you went to prison
for stealin' panties.

241
00:12:37,221 --> 00:12:38,933
How pathetic.

242
00:12:43,442 --> 00:12:46,489
-Hansuke. You seen Katsuko?
-[Hansuke] No.

243
00:12:46,574 --> 00:12:47,909
She was by the boat banner.

244
00:12:47,993 --> 00:12:48,995
[Okabe] Really?

245
00:12:49,078 --> 00:12:53,963
Then I've got a really funny lie for you,
you husband of a whore.

246
00:12:54,046 --> 00:12:56,301
-Don't say that.
-[Hansuke] Stop it. What's wrong?

247
00:12:56,384 --> 00:12:57,428
[Kuma] Got a problem with that?

248
00:13:02,898 --> 00:13:03,941
Where is it?

249
00:13:04,025 --> 00:13:05,486
Sorry.

250
00:13:05,570 --> 00:13:07,031
[Okabe] Katsuko?

251
00:13:07,741 --> 00:13:09,077
Katsuko?

252
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:10,454
