You've got it reversed!

262
00:13:33,416 --> 00:13:37,007
Ryotaro, I'm so ashamed!

263
00:13:39,095 --> 00:13:40,807
Holy shit.

264
00:13:41,391 --> 00:13:43,353
You're all bastards!

265
00:13:44,105 --> 00:13:45,900
[loud clang]

266
00:13:46,025 --> 00:13:48,029
[shouting]

267
00:13:48,321 --> 00:13:49,700
[Masuo] An Olympic flame, huh?

268
00:13:50,158 --> 00:13:51,494
[Ryotaro] You bastards!

269
00:13:55,587 --> 00:13:57,047
Hurry up and do something!

270
00:13:57,131 --> 00:13:59,302
[Hatsutaro] Shut up, you hussy!

271
00:13:59,385 --> 00:14:02,851
You've been sleepin' with Masuo, ain't ya?

272
00:14:03,811 --> 00:14:04,813
What?

273
00:14:04,897 --> 00:14:06,357
You have?

274
00:14:06,441 --> 00:14:08,696
How can you say that, Mitsuyo?
What proof do you have?

275
00:14:08,779 --> 00:14:10,032
I've got proof!

276
00:14:10,115 --> 00:14:16,503
I've watched a ton of porn
about cheatin' wives. I studied them.

277
00:14:16,587 --> 00:14:17,714
That's my proof!

278
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:20,135
-What?
-See?

279
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:21,764
Admit it.

280
00:14:21,847 --> 00:14:24,143
Ask this guy. He knows!

281
00:14:26,064 --> 00:14:28,193
It was you, you shorts-wearing scumbag!

282
00:14:29,236 --> 00:14:32,744
You were nosing around
in all our business.

283
00:14:32,827 --> 00:14:35,123
[Hatsutaro] Is that right?

284
00:14:36,084 --> 00:14:38,798
[Kuma] I thought somethin' was fishy.

285
00:14:39,173 --> 00:14:42,889
There's nobody nowadays
who wants to live in temporary housing.

286
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:47,899
You're a spy for No Season!

287
00:14:47,983 --> 00:14:49,360
-Huh?
-A spy?

288
00:14:52,241 --> 00:14:53,326
That's right.

289
00:14:53,410 --> 00:14:55,205
That's enough, Hansuke.

290
00:14:55,999 --> 00:14:58,546
I sold your personal info

291
00:14:58,921 --> 00:15:02,219
and was paid money by that man!

292
00:15:02,554 --> 00:15:04,306
I'm sorry!

293
00:15:06,770 --> 00:15:10,570
Auntie! Auntie! It's Katsuko! She's…

294
00:15:10,653 --> 00:15:12,741
What's wrong, Okabe?

295
00:15:13,241 --> 00:15:17,041
The kids have barricaded themselves
inside the school building.

296
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:18,878
-Huh?
-What?

297
00:15:18,919 --> 00:15:20,548
-[Okabe] This way!
-[Hasegawa] Ryotaro!

298
00:15:20,631 --> 00:15:21,675
Katsuko!

299
00:15:21,759 --> 00:15:23,011
What's all this?

300
00:15:23,094 --> 00:15:26,267
Watch out! What the heck are you doing?

301
00:15:27,937 --> 00:15:29,983
STAY BACK

302
00:15:30,067 --> 00:15:32,572
[clamoring]

303
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:35,912
Hey!

304
00:15:35,995 --> 00:15:37,122
You okay?

305
00:15:37,624 --> 00:15:40,128
[children] ♪ Lingering like
a juicy tomato ♪

306
00:15:40,212 --> 00:15:43,636
♪ The fickle salad missed the train ♪

307
00:15:43,719 --> 00:15:45,180
It's the Veggie Girls.

308
00:15:45,305 --> 00:15:51,819
♪ While I cry in the triangle corner ♪

309
00:15:51,902 --> 00:15:52,946
Sprouts!

310
00:15:54,533 --> 00:15:55,618
Katsuko!

311
00:15:58,999 --> 00:16:00,210
Tsutomu!

312
00:16:01,212 --> 00:16:03,759
-Stay back!
-[screaming]

313
00:16:05,178 --> 00:16:06,849
[Tsutomu] Stay back!

314
00:16:07,684 --> 00:16:09,896
[loud clamoring]

315
00:16:20,543 --> 00:16:21,628
Oh…

316
00:16:33,819 --> 00:16:35,907
[laughs nervously]

317
00:16:35,990 --> 00:16:38,537
[yelling]

318
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:43,296
[overlapping chatter]

319
00:16:52,941 --> 00:16:55,780
We don't want to leave here!

320
00:16:55,863 --> 00:16:57,617
We wanna stay here forever!

321
00:16:57,700 --> 00:16:59,328
You can't.

322
00:16:59,411 --> 00:17:01,625
They'll start tearing it down tomorrow.

323
00:17:01,708 --> 00:17:02,752
You can't live here!

324
00:17:02,835 --> 00:17:04,714
No! I like it here!

325
00:17:04,798 --> 00:17:06,425
Why do you like it here?

326
00:17:06,510 --> 00:17:08,764
It's where Mom and Dad met.

327
00:17:10,559 --> 00:17:12,229
[emotional music]

328
00:17:12,312 --> 00:17:13,941
[inaudible singing]

329
00:17:14,024 --> 00:17:15,485
[inaudible cheering]

330
00:17:18,032 --> 00:17:21,122
[Mariko] We were all born here.
This is all we know.

331
00:17:21,205 --> 00:17:23,042
So we don't wanna go anywhere else.

332
00:17:23,627 --> 00:17:27,342
Even if it is better than here,
I don't want us to split up!

333
00:17:28,094 --> 00:17:32,185
We talked it over yesterday
and made up our minds to stay here!

334
00:17:32,854 --> 00:17:33,939
Mariko…

335
00:17:34,941 --> 00:17:36,068
I understand.

336
00:17:36,903 --> 00:17:38,156
I understand how you feel.

337
00:17:39,325 --> 00:17:42,623
This place is all I've got too.

338
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:45,671
My whole family died.

339
00:17:46,297 --> 00:17:48,886
All I had was my cat when I came here.

340
00:17:49,512 --> 00:17:51,015
And you know what?

341
00:17:51,725 --> 00:17:53,812
My family abandoned me.

342
00:17:55,190 --> 00:17:56,943
So we understand.

343
00:17:57,695 --> 00:18:01,620
It's called temporary housing,
but to all of you, it's not temporary.

344
00:18:02,872 --> 00:18:06,462
But this doesn't involve Katsuko, right?

345
00:18:06,546 --> 00:18:08,550
Yes, it does.

346
00:18:08,634 --> 00:18:11,932
When we're hungry, we'll eat her.

347
00:18:12,015 --> 00:18:13,351
-What?
-Eat her?

348
00:18:13,434 --> 00:18:14,729
We won't eat her.

349
00:18:14,813 --> 00:18:16,858
We're not going to eat her.

350
00:18:16,942 --> 00:18:19,614
She meant to say
that we'll have her cook for us.

351
00:18:19,698 --> 00:18:21,868
We're not going to split up.

352
00:18:21,952 --> 00:18:25,835
You're lying! Now that Mom's gone,
if we're kicked outta here,

353
00:18:25,918 --> 00:18:28,882
there's no way we'll be able
to live together again.

354
00:18:28,966 --> 00:18:31,847
Yeah, if you weren't my children.

355
00:18:34,351 --> 00:18:35,813
Of course,

356
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:38,694
I know I'm your father.

357
00:18:40,238 --> 00:18:42,910
But if you don't believe that,

358
00:18:43,996 --> 00:18:48,421
then have the man who you think is
your real father take care of you.

359
00:18:48,505 --> 00:18:49,883
Hey!

360
00:18:50,467 --> 00:18:51,887
What about you, Dad?

361
00:18:54,057 --> 00:18:56,353
I'll have to live alone.

362
00:18:57,607 --> 00:19:00,445
It's unfair to take care
of just one of you.

363
00:19:01,948 --> 00:19:04,579
Either all together, or split up.

364
00:19:05,413 --> 00:19:06,541
It's either one.

365
00:19:06,625 --> 00:19:07,627
No!

366
00:19:07,710 --> 00:19:09,379
No, no!

367
00:19:09,463 --> 00:19:10,799
All together is best!

368
00:19:10,883 --> 00:19:12,720
We're all your kids, Dad!

369
00:19:12,803 --> 00:19:14,516
-[Tsutomu] Dad!
-[Mariko] Dad!

370
00:19:14,599 --> 00:19:16,310
-Thank you, you guys.
-Dad!

371
00:19:16,393 --> 00:19:18,356
Ryotaro Sawagami.

372
00:19:18,439 --> 00:19:20,903
[Ryotaro] That's right. Ryotaro Sawagami.

373
00:19:24,201 --> 00:19:28,125
What'll I do?
I don't wanna leave here either.

374
00:19:28,209 --> 00:19:30,213
You've got no choice.

375
00:19:30,296 --> 00:19:32,635
I doubt there's anywhere better than this.

376
00:19:33,804 --> 00:19:37,018
-You've only been here a year.
-But I've gotta go, right?

377
00:19:38,187 --> 00:19:39,398
Yep.

378
00:19:39,481 --> 00:19:43,072
Do I go out quietly
or do I go out fighting?

379
00:19:43,155 --> 00:19:44,283
Fighting?

380
00:19:45,451 --> 00:19:47,707
-[screams]
-Whoa! You scared me!

381
00:19:47,790 --> 00:19:49,878
I've had enough of this!

382
00:19:49,961 --> 00:19:53,092
-[Tatsuya] Hey! Stop! Stop!
-[Hansuke] Outta my way!

383
00:19:53,217 --> 00:19:55,723
[screaming]

384
00:19:56,390 --> 00:19:59,647
Back off! Back off, you scum!

385
00:19:59,731 --> 00:20:01,483
Back off!

386
00:20:02,110 --> 00:20:04,406
This is mine!

387
00:20:04,489 --> 00:20:07,162
This belongs to me! It's mine!

388
00:20:07,245 --> 00:20:09,416
[indistinct chatter]

389
00:20:09,959 --> 00:20:11,504
-Hey!
-Let go!

390
00:20:12,130 --> 00:20:13,967
[worker] What do you think you're doing?

391
00:20:20,063 --> 00:20:22,067
What the heck have you done?

392
00:20:22,860 --> 00:20:24,864
[screaming continues]

393
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:30,876
[Tatsuya] Quit filming!
You're trespassing!

394
00:20:30,959 --> 00:20:32,880
[Mitsuyo] Stop it! Stop it!

395
00:20:34,007 --> 00:20:36,178
[Kuniko] Roku-chan's missing!

396
00:20:36,261 --> 00:20:38,391
[Tatsuya] One at a time, please!

397
00:20:38,474 --> 00:20:40,186
Roku-chan's missing!

398
00:20:40,269 --> 00:20:43,192
My husband got drunk
and set fire to Shima-san's place!

399
00:20:43,275 --> 00:20:44,696
Hansuke!

400
00:20:44,779 --> 00:20:47,702
-Hansuke!
-[Mitsuyo] This way!

401
00:20:49,789 --> 00:20:52,962
[distant whooping]

402
00:20:53,379 --> 00:20:55,383
[boisterous laughter]

403
00:20:55,592 --> 00:20:58,097
-[Hansuke] Shima-san!
-[Masuo] At last, you came out.

404
00:20:58,180 --> 00:21:00,309
At last, you came out.

405
00:21:00,393 --> 00:21:02,815
It'll be fine.
They're tearing it down anyway.

406
00:21:02,898 --> 00:21:04,694
-This'll make it easier.
-My sweet wife!

407
00:21:04,777 --> 00:21:07,658
-Have a drink.
-My sweet wife's inside!

408
00:21:08,159 --> 00:21:10,831
What? Why didn't you say so sooner?

409
00:21:11,331 --> 00:21:13,210
No, Shima-san!

410
00:21:13,962 --> 00:21:16,050
Oh no! What have I done?

411
00:21:16,133 --> 00:21:19,014
-Hatsu, what have I done?
-Fire extinguisher!

412
00:21:19,097 --> 00:21:20,559
Get a fire extinguisher!

413
00:21:20,642 --> 00:21:22,312
You need the fire department.

414
00:21:22,395 --> 00:21:25,986
The wind's pretty strong,
so it'll burn quickly.

415
00:21:26,487 --> 00:21:27,656
Huh?

416
00:21:28,282 --> 00:21:31,790
Hurry up and call the fire department.

417
00:21:33,543 --> 00:21:34,670
[exclaims]

418
00:21:35,004 --> 00:21:36,131
Roku-chan?

419
00:21:36,215 --> 00:21:39,429
-[Hansuke] Shima-san!
-[screaming]

420
00:21:39,514 --> 00:21:40,724
Hansuke!

421
00:21:41,559 --> 00:21:44,106
-[Shima's wife] I've got no choice now.
-[Yoshie] Huh?

422
00:21:44,524 --> 00:21:46,986
[shouting]

423
00:21:51,871 --> 00:21:54,126
Oh my God!

424
00:21:55,712 --> 00:21:58,175
Dodes'ka-den. Dodes'ka-den.

425
00:21:58,259 --> 00:22:01,098
[uproarious shouting]

426
00:22:08,822 --> 00:22:10,951
-Dodes…
-[distant shouting]

427
00:22:13,874 --> 00:22:15,334
Watch out! Watch out!

428
00:22:15,418 --> 00:22:17,715
Okay! Bring it on!

429
00:22:19,467 --> 00:22:20,596
I don't know how.

430
00:22:22,390 --> 00:22:24,896
I don't know how to stop it!

431
00:22:24,979 --> 00:22:27,275
-Roku-chan!
-Roku-chan!

432
00:22:27,358 --> 00:22:29,906
-Roku-chan!
-[uproarious shouting]

433
00:22:32,285 --> 00:22:34,665
[shattering, crashing]

434
00:22:34,749 --> 00:22:36,126
Mom!

435
00:22:37,128 --> 00:22:39,842
-Mom…
-[explosion]

436
00:22:42,723 --> 00:22:44,267
I'm sick of this!

437
00:22:48,818 --> 00:22:50,321
Trains are better after all.

438
00:22:52,660 --> 00:22:53,787
Hey!

439
00:22:53,870 --> 00:22:56,458
-Mom! Mom!
-Roku-chan!

440
00:22:56,542 --> 00:22:58,588
Mom! Mom!

441
00:22:59,590 --> 00:23:01,218
-Are you hurt anywhere?
-No.

442
00:23:02,262 --> 00:23:03,974
[resident 1] Hansuke! You okay?

443
00:23:05,267 --> 00:23:07,898
[Tatsuya] Hansuke!

444
00:23:07,982 --> 00:23:10,194
[resident 1] Is he dead?

445
00:23:10,278 --> 00:23:12,282
[Tatsuya] He's alive! Hansuke!

446
00:23:12,365 --> 00:23:14,369
[clamoring]

447
00:23:14,912 --> 00:23:16,833
[crying]

448
00:23:17,333 --> 00:23:20,047
[resident 2]
It's all burning down. Oh, dear!

449
00:23:28,063 --> 00:23:30,694
-[sneezes]
-[all gasping]

450
00:23:43,135 --> 00:23:46,601
[Katsuko starts laughing]

451
00:24:00,169 --> 00:24:02,173
Awesome!

452
00:24:02,256 --> 00:24:04,052
Awesome!

453
00:24:05,806 --> 00:24:08,185
[cheering]

454
00:24:15,867 --> 00:24:18,623
[Tatsuya] Awesome!

455
00:24:20,209 --> 00:24:22,923
We did it!

456
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:29,770
[Hansuke] And that's how
we went out fighting.

457
00:24:38,412 --> 00:24:39,790
SQUATTERS IN TEMPORARY HOUSING
BURN AND RIOT

458
00:24:39,874 --> 00:24:43,756
The riot that day got replayed
again and again on tabloid TV shows.

459
00:24:43,840 --> 00:24:46,470
It went viral for a week on social media.

460
00:24:46,554 --> 00:24:48,182
[Tatsuya] You're trespassing!

461
00:24:48,265 --> 00:24:50,352
[Hansuke] Who said you could film, dammit?

462
00:24:51,354 --> 00:24:53,610
Long after that,

463
00:24:53,693 --> 00:24:58,410
the former residents never spoke about
how they lived in that town.

464
00:24:58,995 --> 00:25:00,790
Even if they crossed paths,

465
00:25:01,499 --> 00:25:03,880
they would absolutely never
talk to each other.

466
00:25:04,507 --> 00:25:07,220
It was an unwritten rule.

467
00:25:07,303 --> 00:25:09,265
Don't interfere with

468
00:25:09,349 --> 00:25:12,606
former friends hiding their past
and blending into society.

469
00:25:12,689 --> 00:25:14,860
See how it looks in the mirror.

470
00:25:16,989 --> 00:25:19,787
That's lovely. Are you looking for a top?

471
00:25:19,870 --> 00:25:22,291
-[gleeful shouting]
-Dodes'ka-den. Dodes'ka-den.

472
00:25:23,001 --> 00:25:24,462
Dodes'ka-den.

473
00:25:25,339 --> 00:25:30,015
The event commemorating reconstruction
was ultimately never held.

474
00:25:31,059 --> 00:25:36,821
The town without seasons no longer exists.

475
00:25:37,405 --> 00:25:40,912
There is one thing that they did learn.

476
00:25:42,039 --> 00:25:44,587
There is no worse way to live.

477
00:25:45,129 --> 00:25:48,385
But there is also
no more human way to live.

478
00:25:50,306 --> 00:25:51,851
I see.

479
00:25:53,270 --> 00:25:55,525
Personally, I like it.

480
00:25:56,276 --> 00:25:57,904
But it can't be published like this.

481
00:26:02,998 --> 00:26:04,417
[editor] Mr. Tanaka?

482
00:26:06,296 --> 00:26:07,758
Yeah, you're right.

483
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:10,555
The characters are captivating.

484
00:26:10,639 --> 00:26:13,435
Like the homeless father and son
and train crazy Roku-chan.

485
00:26:13,519 --> 00:26:14,813
A TOWN WITHOUT SEASONS

486
00:26:14,897 --> 00:26:16,399
People like that don't exist.

487
00:26:17,485 --> 00:26:19,656
But ethically,

488
00:26:20,407 --> 00:26:23,080
"ganmodoki" and "sprouts" won't do.

489
00:26:23,623 --> 00:26:26,796
Disrespecting women is a problem.
I liked those though.

490
00:26:26,879 --> 00:26:27,923
[meows]

491
00:26:28,131 --> 00:26:32,766
Next time, please write something
heartwarming where nobody gets hurt.

492
00:26:34,018 --> 00:26:35,396
Thank you for coming all this way.

493
00:26:36,356 --> 00:26:37,943
Thank you.

494
00:26:38,235 --> 00:26:40,406
[laughs]

495
00:26:51,637 --> 00:26:53,599
PLAYING SHOGI WITHOUT PAWNS
IS PLAYING A LOSING GAME OF SHOGI

496
00:26:53,683 --> 00:26:55,394
[laughs]

497
00:27:02,032 --> 00:27:04,955
THE END

498
00:27:05,038 --> 00:27:07,919
[closing theme music]

499
